en's swimming 50-meter freestyle on Sunday.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3191, \"end\": 3196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5818460962677537, \"rank\": 0.7186067762717673, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nail-biting finish  The Olympic mixed 4 x 100m medley relay swimming competition saw an incredibly close race on Saturday.\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.142164158873115e-35, \"text\": \"medley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medley_swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. team won the gold after narrowly edging out the Chinese team by 0.12 seconds.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3559, \"end\": 3566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.968562458416852, \"rank\": 0.020255969647544343, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race featured several lead changes and tense competition in one of the most exciting heats of the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Cover: China's gold medallists (C) Chen Qingchen and Jia Yifan, silver medallists (L) Liu Shengshu and Tan Ning, and Japan's bronze medallists (R) Nami Matsuyama and Chiharu Shida celebrate on the podium with their medals during the women's doubles badminton medal ceremony in the Paris 2024 Olympic Games at Porte de la Chapelle Arena in Paris, France, August 3, 2024.\